description:
Job Highlights 

Solid exp in e-Commerce & Social Media 2-3 years
Work independently for operating an online shop
Knowledge use of web page, photoshop & AI design marketing materials

Job Description

A newly set up on-line shop is looking for a competent, reliable and agile candidate to fill up a position of E-Commence Officer to manage and boost the sales of our  e-Commerce platforms including but not limited to our online shops, to design and prepare marketing materials for both the online shops and showroom.

Duties and Responsibilities

Fully responsible to operate this online shop and showroom independently;
Responsibilities including but not limited to online sales, marketing and daily Operation of this online shop;
Perform & manage operation of this online shop and on different selling channels and  E-Commerce portals; 
Manage daily operations of online shop including generate & update website content (product listing, data entry, promotions, etc);
Effective use of SEO, social media and KOLs to promote our products, e.g. through Facebook, Instagram, Google AD, WeChat group and 小紅書 etc;
Knowledge of video shooting, editing and daily video production;
Analyze and monitor online shop statistics and daily sales data to optimize channel traffic performance and sales; 
Modify weekly product arrangements and make suggestions to change online shop layouts; 
Create & implement tactical offers to support specific products and target specific market;
Other ad-hoc assignments.

Requirements

Degree in Journalism & Communication or related discipline;
2+ year relevant experience in E-commerce platform related, (fresh graduated will be considered);
Possess well-developed design skills and marketing knowledge – capable to use photoshops, AI for design and preparing marketing materials;
Good knowledge of SEO, SEM, Goggle analytics and adwords;
Experience with logistic arrangement and warehouse management is advantage;
Proficient in MS Office (MS Word, Excel, Powerpoint, Outlook);
Capable to work independently;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (include Mandarin).

Availability commencement :

Around February, 2022 (after CNY holiday)

Working days :

5 days per week

Tue–Sat (09:30~18:30); Sun & Mon Rest day

Reporting to Digital Manager, APAC, the position will support the formulation of eCommerce strategies for APAC region.  He/she will be responsible for the execution of local digital marketing campaigns to generate traffic, the identification and coordination of local promotions, and the enrichment and optimization of local product descriptions in digital channels, to strategically grow online sales in a specific location.

Key Accountabilities:

Support Digital Manager, APAC and Global teams to implement vision, roadmaps and program backlog of the local eCommerce strategy;
Strategically grow eCommerce ahead of the market in specific location;
Identify and coordinate local promotions and launch of new products within the eCommerce area;
Tailor portfolio of opportunities in eCommerce to local market to make it a platform for growth – including through partnerships with brands and communication initiatives;
Work with global Product Owners and Product Managers to implement the local digital strategy to improve traffic acquisition, sales and conversion of the eCommerce site (including SEO/SEM, A/B testing initiatives);
Optimize end-to-end region-specific customer journeys by devising new solutions, services, products or propositions; and
Identify and implement new opportunities throughout the customer journey to deliver high performing, agile customer interactions and touchpoints.
Requirements

Degree in Business Management, Marketing, E-commerce or relevant disciplines;
3-5 years of digital marketing / eCommerce experience; China exposure is a must;
Proven knowledge of standard concepts, practices, and procedures within the retail and/or travel industry (with a strong focus on eCommerce);
Strong background in digital marketing principles such as funnel optimization UX, SEO & Landing Page optimization & Display expertise in customer journey management, digital and communications;
Experience in working with UX/UI designers to define customer experiences;
Experience in Adobe tools (e.g., Magento, marketing tools) and Google Analytics desirable;
Experience in running A/B tests for campaigns and deriving customer insights a major plus;
Demonstrable experience coordinating SEO/SEM, marketing database, email, social media and/or display advertising campaigns;
Deep understanding in all the commercial levers to drive performance (range, price, experience, marketing);
Commercial yet customer-first mindset with the ability to identify customer needs; and
Proficiency in both English and Chinese, especially Mandarin and written Chinese. 
Interested parties, please send full CV with availability, current and expected salary to us by clicking below button “Apply Now”.



We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Personal data collected will be treated in strict confidence and handled confidentially by authorised personnel for recruitment-related purposes only within Dufry Group of companies.

Responsibilities


Manage and create content for various social media platforms, including copywriting, product descriptions translation, and photos / videos editing;
Assist in planning and implementing online and offline marketing campaigns and events;
Affiliate marketing coordination. To grow the number of influencers and followers for the brands;
Liaise with the operations team and design team;
Perform ad-hoc tasks as assigned.
Requirements

Diploma holder or above in Communication, Business, Marketing or related field;
2 years of solid experience in marketing, e-commerce, or retail is highly preferred;
Proficiency in managing social media platforms, Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, and video editing;
Independent, self-motivated, detail-minded, and a good team player;
Good command of written & spoken English, Mandarin, and Cantonese;
Immediately available is a definite advantage


Interest parties, please send full resume with current and expected salary and date of availability by clicking "Apply Now". Personal data provided in application will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purpose by MARYLING only. All unsuccessful applications will be destroyed upon completion of the process.

Job Description

Responsibilities:

         Build and manage the new brand own e-shop and e-commerce activities for local market;
         Oversee e-commerce platforms to achieve sales targets, enhance brand awareness and ensure high standard of customer services;
         Manage daily operations of brand own e-shop, sales order monitoring, sales forecast, inventory planning, promotional arrangement and reports;
         Formulate digital marketing plan to improve traffic and conversion rate;
         Set the strategic direction, oversee and co-ordinate all e-commerce activities through different media;
         Conduct market & competitor research to understand customer needs for enhancing customer shopping experience;
         Collaborate with management team on corporate e-commerce strategies;

Requirements:

         Diploma or above in e-Commerce, Digital Marketing, Marketing, Business, IT or related disciplines;
         3 years relevant experience in retail e-Commerce / digital marketing portals;
         Solid experience in building & managing on-line shop portals, digital campaigns and advertisement;
         Experience in FMCG e-commerce and online channels is an advantage;
         Strong business sense and analytical skills;
         Excellent presentation and communication skills and able to work fast-paced working environment;
         Well organized, positive and energetic, strong team player and ability to work independently;
         Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese;
         More experience will be considered as Supervisor
Interested candidates, please contact us at 28919882 for company details before applying.

Responsibilities:

Develop and execute digital marketing promotion & campaign in website and other digital platforms according to company’s guidelines;
Propose and develop creative ideas that resonate with the target audience for different products & campaigns;
Prepare creative and write-up for content marketing/ online promotion/ digital campaign;
Manage all information and product description in website and of the US wholesalers or any promotional channels;
Implement and coordinate with team members in copy-writing and video production projects and script-writing;
Handle customer enquiries via digital/eCommerce platforms;
Manage and Monitor project progress, from planning to execution, from copywriting to creating visual assets;
Assist in ad-hoc marketing project

Requirements:

Bachelor Degree holder or above in Communications, Marketing or other related disciplines;
Minimum 3 years relevant experience in digital marketing; 
Experience in eCommerce platform operations and website maintenance is preferable;
Previous experience with eCommerce marketing such as Amazon is desirable;
Sharp marketing sense, able to multi-tasking and good time-management;
Strong interpersonal and communication skills and attentive to details;

Self motivated with ability to undertake independent initiatives;
Excellent writing and communication skills and good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese (including Cantonese and Mandarin);
Immediately available is preferred

Responsibilities

Responsible for executing strategic plans to achieve sales targets and expand the customer base in eCommerce channel specialize in overseas marketplace;
To develop and execute full spectrum of marketing and sales plans including budget, brand management, product pricing and trade marketing programs;
Work close with different teams to monitor and improve operations including but not limited to order management, fulfillment, order forecast, inventory management, preparing business analysis reports;
Manage product mix and assortment planning on assigned platforms;
Analyze business trends and consumer insights and evaluate existing product categories on choices;
Suggest appropriate go-to-market strategies and plans;
Work closely with 3rd party platforms, agencies & in-house designers for marketing service support and ad hoc projects;
Lead a team to ensure smooth operation in various channels and drive sales to support a fast growing businesses.
Requirements

University graduate with at least 5 years’ experience in eCommerce/ retail management preferred;
Knowledge across SEM, Social Media and Affiliates;
Experienced in cross-border marketplaces and eCommerce operations is absolutely advantage;
Good in numerical sense;
Hard-working with positive attitude;
Able to work under pressure and meet the deadlines;
Detail-oriented, with a high level of accuracy and ability to process and analyze data;
Fast learner and willing to face challenges;
Strong communication in written and spoken English, Cantonese, with Putonghua is an advantage;
Proficiency in MS Office including MS Excel.


We offer

5 - day work week
Medical Benefits
Annual Merit Bonus
Staff Purchase Discounts
Staff Recreation Activity
Shuttle Bus Service
Education Sponsorship

